/**
28 
 * Provides Base64 encoding and decoding as defined by RFC 2045.
29 
 *
30 
 * <p>
31 
 * This class implements section <cite>6.8. Base64 Content-Transfer-Encoding</cite> from RFC 2045 <cite>Multipurpose
32 
 * Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) Part One: Format of Internet Message Bodies</cite> by Freed and Borenstein.
33 
 * </p>
34 
 *
35 
 * @see <a href="http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2045.txt">RFC 2045</a>
36 
 * @author Apache Software Foundation
37 
 * @since 1.0-dev
38 
 * @version $Id$
39 
 */
40 
public class Base64 implements BinaryEncoder, BinaryDecoder {
41
42 
    /**
43 
     * Chunk size per RFC 2045 section 6.8.
44 
     *
45 
     * <p>
46 
     * The {@value} character limit does not count the trailing CRLF, but counts all other characters, including any
47 
     * equal signs.
48 
     * </p>
49 
     *
50 
     * @see <a href="http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2045.txt">RFC 2045 section 6.8</a>
51 
     */
52 
    static final int CHUNK_SIZE = 76;
53
54 
    /**
55 
     * Chunk separator per RFC 2045 section 2.1.
56 
     *
57 
     * @see <a href="http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2045.txt">RFC 2045 section 2.1</a>
58 
     */
59 
    static final byte[] CHUNK_SEPARATOR = "\r\n".getBytes();
60
61 
    /**
62 
     * The base length.

     */

    private static final int BASELENGTH = 255;
65
66 
    /**
67 
     * Lookup length.
68 
     */
69 
    private static final int LOOKUPLENGTH = 64;

    /**

     * Used to calculate the number of bits in a byte.

     */

    private static final int EIGHTBIT = 8;

    /**

     */

    /**

     * Used to determine how many bits data contains.
83 
     */

    private static final int TWENTYFOURBITGROUP = 24;

    /**

     * Used to get the number of Quadruples.

     */

    /**

    private static final int SIGN = -128;

    /**
97 
     * Byte used to pad output.
98 
     */
99 
    private static final byte PAD = (byte) '=';
100
101 
    /**
102 
     * Contains the Base64 values <code>0</code> through <code>63</code> accessed by using character encodings as
103 
     * indices.
104 
     * <p>
105 
     * For example, <code>base64Alphabet['+']</code> returns <code>62</code>.
106 
     * </p>
107 
     * <p>
108 
     * The value of undefined encodings is <code>-1</code>.
109 
     * </p>
110 
     */
111 
    private static final byte[] base64Alphabet = new byte[BASELENGTH];
112
113 
    /**
114 
     * <p>
115 
     * Contains the Base64 encodings <code>A</code> through <code>Z</code>, followed by <code>a</code> through
116 
     * <code>z</code>, followed by <code>0</code> through <code>9</code>, followed by <code>+</code>, and
117 
     * <code>/</code>.
118 
     * </p>
119 
     * <p>
120 
     * This array is accessed by using character values as indices.
121 
     * </p>
122 
     * <p>
123 
     * For example, <code>lookUpBase64Alphabet[62] </code> returns <code>'+'</code>.
124 
     * </p>
125 
     */
126 
    private static final byte[] lookUpBase64Alphabet = new byte[LOOKUPLENGTH];
127
128 
    // Populating the lookup and character arrays
129 
    static {
130 
        for (int i = 0; i < BASELENGTH; i++) {
131 
            base64Alphabet[i] = (byte) -1;
132 
        }
133 
        for (int i = 'Z'; i >= 'A'; i--) {
134 
            base64Alphabet[i] = (byte) (i - 'A');
135 
        }
136 
        for (int i = 'z'; i >= 'a'; i--) {
137 
            base64Alphabet[i] = (byte) (i - 'a' + 26);
138 
        }
139 
        for (int i = '9'; i >= '0'; i--) {
140 
            base64Alphabet[i] = (byte) (i - '0' + 52);
141 
        }
142
143 
        base64Alphabet['+'] = 62;
144 
        base64Alphabet['/'] = 63;
145
146 
        for (int i = 0; i <= 25; i++) {
147 
            lookUpBase64Alphabet[i] = (byte) ('A' + i);
148 
        }
149
150 
        for (int i = 26, j = 0; i <= 51; i++, j++) {
151 
            lookUpBase64Alphabet[i] = (byte) ('a' + j);
152 
        }
153
154 
        for (int i = 52, j = 0; i <= 61; i++, j++) {
155 
            lookUpBase64Alphabet[i] = (byte) ('0' + j);
156 
        }
157
158 
        lookUpBase64Alphabet[62] = (byte) '+';
159 
        lookUpBase64Alphabet[63] = (byte) '/';
160 
    }
